cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Synesis: A DSL compiler for knowledge engineering"
abstract: >
  synesis-explorer is the VSCode extension for the Synesis ecosystem. It provides
  tree-view explorers for codes, ontology, references, and relations extracted from
  .syn annotation files, integrated with the synesis-lsp Language Server for
  real-time validation and the synesis-coder LLM annotation assistant.
authors:
  - family-names: De Britto
    given-names: Christian Maciel
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1431-3924"
version: "0.5.30"
date-released: "2026-06-16"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/synesis-lang/synesis-explorer"
url: "https://synesis-lang.github.io/synesis-docs"
keywords:
  - qualitative-research
  - knowledge-engineering
  - vscode-extension
  - synesis
